<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idefb3af9f-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s4206"><num value="4206">§ 4206.</num><heading> Grants, contracts, etc., authority</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may carry out the purposes of this chapter, with existing facilities and funds otherwise available, through the use of grants, contracts, or such other means as the Secretary deems appropriate.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idefb3afa0-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/97/98/tXV/s1545">Pub. L. 97–98, title XV, § 1545</ref>, <date date="1981-12-22">Dec. 22, 1981</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/95/1343">95 Stat. 1343</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idefb3afa1-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idefb3afa2-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idefb3afa3-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective six months after <date date="1981-12-22">Dec. 22, 1981</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/97/98/s1549">section 1549 of Pub. L. 97–98</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t7/s4201">section 4201 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
